  "text": "Hence, according to one set of related views, the congruency effect indexes a cognitive mechanism that is shared with processing in other contexts that also require a self-other distinction. Consequently, a self-other distinction underpinned by right temporoparietal junction has been argued to play a broader role in social cognition more generally, including autism, empathy and theory of mind [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
